# Operator service: trickle a plate into a running long-lived campaign tree.
#
# The bb_operator sidecar resolves the currently active task (from
# /skill_server/task_state) and appends a plate dict onto
# `persistent.plate_queue` in that task's SQLite blackboard. The campaign
# tree's PopFromQueue picks it up on the next iteration boundary.
#
# `cadence_min` and `target_cycles` apply per-plate; if zero they fall back
# to the campaign default. `imaging_protocol` selects which ImagePlate
# protocol the per-cycle subtree should run.

string plate_name              # unique plate id (matches Liconic registry)
string barcode                 # optional barcode for cross-reference
int32 target_cycles            # 0 → campaign default
int32 cadence_min              # 0 → campaign default
string imaging_protocol        # blank → campaign default
int32 liconic_slot             # 0 → wherever Liconic puts it
---
bool success
string message
string task_id                 # the task into which the plate was queued
